headline: Home Builders Are Shrugging Off Trump’s Tariffs. This Is Their Worry.
summary: “Home buyers are moving more slowly in making their purchase decisions,” Jeffrey Mezger, CEO of the $4.2 billion  KB Home  said on an earnings conference call Monday.  Buyers shopping for homes built by the $31 billion  Lennar  are similarly gun-shy.  “While there continues to be considerable traffic of customers looking for homes, the urgency to actually transact remained tepid,”  Lennar  co-CEO Stuart Miller said earlier this month.

headline: 1 Large-Cap Stock on Our Watchlist and 2 to Brush Off
summary: Large-cap stocks are known for their staying power and ability to weather market storms better than smaller competitors. However, their sheer size makes it more challenging to maintain high growth rates as they’ve already captured significant portions of their markets.
